<HEADLINE> Jeter Leaves With Abdominal Strain  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Yankees shortstop Derek Jeter left Thursday
night's game against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays after the second
inning with an abdominal strain in his left side.
</P>
<P>
   ''It will probably be a few days,'' Yankees manager Joe Torre
said. ''I think we have to wait through the weekend and see how it
responds to treatment and then make a decision.''
</P>
