<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Ex-Norfolk State Coaches Indicted  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Four former Norfolk State coaches have been
indicted on forgery charges.
</P>
<P>
   The Circuit Court indictments, returned April 5, were based on
an investigation of alleged travel expense irregularities. Those
charged were former track coach Steven Earl Riddick; his assistant,
Simon N. Hodnett; former basketball coach Melvin L. Coleman; and
his assistant, Erik Tyrone Rashad.
</P>
<P>
   Riddick, a member of the 400-meter relay team that won a gold
medal in the 1976 Olympics, also was charged with misappropriation
of public funds.
</P>
<P>
   Riddick ran an Olympic training program at the university for
foreign athletes, but it ended in 1998 when Olympic officials
yanked funding and questioned Riddick's spending practices.
Athletes complained about inadequate housing and medical coverage.
</P>
<P>
   Riddick, 48, of Hampton, faces nine counts of forgery and one
count of misappropriation. Rashad, 37, of Tampa, Fla., faces nine
counts of forgery. Coleman, 57, of Weirton, W.Va., faces five
counts of forgery. Hodnett, 33, of Virginia Beach, faces five
counts of forgery.
</P>
<P>
   Neither prosecutors nor school officials would say how much
money was involved.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
