<HEADLINE> Tornadoes in Iowa Injure at Least 8  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DUNKERTON, Iowa (AP) -- A dozen tornadoes struck northeastern
Iowa late Thursday, injuring at least eight people, damaging
buildings and forcing the evacuation of a nursing home.
</P>
<P>
   The tornadoes cut a swath of damage about 1{ miles wide
beginning just north of the Waterloo airport, through Dunkerton and
into Buchanan County, said Black Hawk County sheriff's Deputy Tony
Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fortunately, it did not go through any densely populated
areas,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   An elderly woman was in critical condition after a tornado
struck her home in Cedar Falls.
</P>
<P>
   About 150 tenants of a nursing home in Black Hawk County were
evacuated after its roof was heavily damaged. Up to seven suffered
minor injuries, said Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   Police told the National Weather Service that a co-op elevator
was heavily damaged and a church roof was blown off in Dunkerton,
which is 120 miles northeast of Des Moines. A farmhouse was
destroyed as were seven outbuildings, and a storm spotter said two
houses were destroyed in town.
</P>
<P>
   The storms, which also produced hail and heavy rain, were moving
slowly to the east.
</P>
</TEXT>
