<HEADLINE> NBA Today  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated PressSCOREBOARD:
Friday, May 12:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Miami at New York (8 p.m. EDT). The Heat try to regain homecourt
advantage and take a 2-1 lead in the best-of-seven series.
STARS:
Thursday:
</P>
<P>
   -- Arvydas Sabonis and Steve Smith, Trail Blazers. Sabonis had 22
points on 10-for-13 shooting with eight rebounds, and Smith had 21
points and six assists as Portland beat Utah 103-84 for a 3-0 lead
in the Western Conference semifinal series.
SPARKPLUG:
</P>
<P>
   Bonzi Wells, the last person off Portland's bench on Thursday
night, scored 19 points in 15 minutes, helping the Trail Blazers
defeat Utah 103-84. Wells, who was 8-13 from the field, scored 10
points in the fourth quarter as the Blazers held off a second-half
Jazz surge. Utah is one game from a sweep in a best-of-seven series
for the first time in franchise history.
STRONG IN DEFEAT:
</P>
<P>
   Karl Malone turned in a double-double performance with a
game-high 28 points and 11 rebounds for Utah, but he had only two
points in the fourth quarter as the Jazz were outscored 28-14 and
lost 103-84 in Game 3 to Portland on Thursday night. Teammate Jeff
Hornacek, who is ending his 14-year NBA career, added 24 points.
SHARING HONORS:
</P>
<P>
   Chicago's Elton Brand and Houston's Steve Francis, the first two
picks in last summer's draft, were co-winners of the NBA's Rookie
of the Year Award, announced Thursday. Brand and Francis each
received 58 of a possible 121 votes from a panel of sportswriters
and broadcasters. Lamar Odom of the Los Angeles Clippers and
Cleveland's Andre Miller also received votes. It's only the third
time two rookies have shared the honor. Dallas' Jason Kidd and
Detroit's Grant Hill were co-winners in 1994-95, as were Boston's
Dave Cowens and Portland's Geoff Petrie in 1970-71.
SOLD:
</P>
<P>
   The sale of the Vancouver Grizzlies to Michael Heisley was
finalized on Thursday when details of the $160 million purchase of
the NBA team from Orca Bay Sports and Entertainment were completed.
The Grizzlies are now owned solely by Hoops L.P., a company owned
by Heisley, a Chicago businessman who made millions turning
money-losing businesses into profitable ventures.
SURGERY:
</P>
<P>
   Golden State forward Donyell Marshall underwent successful
surgery on his right wrist Thursday. The team said the arthroscopic
procedure repaired torn cartilage in the wrist. Marshall was one of
eight players in the NBA this season to average double figures in
points (14.2) and rebounds (10.0), playing 64 games this season.
SPEAKING:
</P>
<P>
   ''If I was in the crowd, I'd have left too. If we'd have lost
these games by one or two or four, I'd think there would be more
hope.'' -- Utah guard Jeff Hornacek after the Jazz lost 103-84 to
Portland on Thursday night, falling behind 3-0 in their
best-of-seven Western Conference semifinal series.
</P>
</TEXT>
