<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guerillas Attack Israel Militiamen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) -- Guerrillas attacked Israeli-allied
militiamen in southern Lebanon on Friday, killing one and wounding
another, Lebanese security officials said. The attacks provoked
Israeli shelling.
</P>
<P>
   The guerrillas fired rockets and mortar shells at four outposts
manned by militiamen of the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army in a
southern Lebanon border enclave held by Israel, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The wounded militiaman was airlifted to Israel for treatment,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the attacks,
to which Israeli troops and SLA militiamen responded by firing at
suspected guerrilla hide-outs near villages on the edge of the
enclave, the officials said. There were no reports of casualties
from the shelling.
</P>
<P>
   In Jerusalem, the Israeli army acknowledged the death of an SLA
man and that another was wounded in Friday's fighting.
</P>
<P>
   An Israeli army statement also said Israeli warplanes attacked
''terrorist targets'' in areas outside the occupied zone Thursday
night. The airstrikes were apparently in response to attacks by
Iranian-backed Hezbollah guerrillas on Israeli and SLA outposts in
the occupied zone.
</P>
<P>
   Last Sunday, an SLA militiaman was killed in a Hezbollah attack.
</P>
<P>
   Hezbollah, or the Party of God, is leading the campaign to oust
Israeli troops and the SLA from the border enclave held by the
Jewish state since 1985 as a buffer against cross-border guerrilla
attacks on its northern towns.
</P>
<P>
   Israel plans to withdraw its troops from southern Lebanon by
July.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
