<HEADLINE> Economic Report Pushes Stocks Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks moved higher this morning on Wall Street
after a government report showed a decline in wholesale prices in
April, helping to quell recent worries about inflationary
pressures.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average was up 80.28 at 10,626.25 in
mid-morning trading.
</P>
