<HEADLINE> Bond Prices Fall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Treasury bond prices were lower at midday.
</P>
<P>
   The price of the Treasury's 10-year note was down 13-32 point,
or $4.06\ per $1,000 in face value, around midday, while its yield
rose to 6.46 percent from 6.40 percent late Thursday. Prices and
yields move in opposite directions.
</P>
<P>
   The 30-year bonds fell 1-32 point and yielded 6.14 percent,
unchanged from late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Yields on three-month Treasury bills rose to 6.14 percent as the
discount rose 0.05 percentage point to 5.98 percent. Six-month
yields rose to 6.47 percent as the discount rose 0.05 percentage
point to 6.19 percent. One-year yields rose to 6.35 percent as the
discount rose 0.06 point to 6.04 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the
discount is the interest at which they are sold.
</P>
</TEXT>
