<HEADLINE> Jury: Old Woman Was Scared to Death  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SPRINGFIELD, Ohio (AP) -- A burglar was convicted of scaring a
79-year-old woman to death.
</P>
<P>
   Mary Virginia Jones went screaming into the night after hearing
the sound of breaking glass and seeing an intruder kick in her
kitchen door Feb. 1. After reaching a neighbor's house, she
suffered a heart attack and was hospitalized. She died 27 days
later.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, a jury found 39-year-old handyman Clarence Farmer
guilty of involuntary manslaughter, in addition to burglary. He
could get up to 18 years in prison at sentencing May 23.
</P>
<P>
   ''He put her into the hospital,'' prosecutor David Smith said.
''He put her through hell. He didn't mean to kill her. I don't mean
that. I mean he should be held responsible for his actions.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones had befriended Farmer and paid him to weed, mow and
perform other odd jobs.
</P>
</TEXT>
