<HEADLINE> Bahamas Exchange Opens  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) -- The Bahamas International Securities
Exchange conducted its first day of floor trading of local stocks
Friday, and reported no glitches during the abbreviated session.
</P>
<P>
   Two member firms traded nine listed local stocks during the
two-hours session that ended at noon. The exchange will normally
operate Monday through Friday from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're just kicking our legs out and stretching this morning,''
said D'Arcy Rahming, chief operations officer of the exchange.
</P>
<P>
   Hiram Cox, a trader with Colina Financial Advisors, said 20
orders were entered into the system with about 2,300 shares traded.
Colina and Fidelity are the two firms approved to trade on the
exchange and two other firms have applied to become members,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The international component of the exchange is still being
developed and is scheduled to open in late 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
