<HEADLINE> Padres Shuffle Bullpen Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- The San Diego Padres shuffled their pitching
staff Friday, demoting a starter and a reliever and promoting a
starter and two relievers from Triple-A Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   The Padres also placed right-handed reliever Rodney Myers on the
60-day disabled list and announced he will undergo surgery on
Saturday to repair a torn tendon in his left knee he suffered
Thursday on the artificial turf in Cincinnati. Myers is expected to
miss the rest of the year.
</P>
<P>
   The Padres recalled Brandon Kolb and purchased the contracts of
Stan Spencer and Matt Whiteside from Las Vegas. Spencer is
scheduled to start Saturday against Todd Stottlemyre.
</P>
<P>
   To make room on the roster, starter Rodrigo Lopez was optioned
and reliever Vicente Palacios was outrighted, both to Vegas. All
pitchers involved in the moves are right-handers.
</P>
<P>
   Spencer was 4-0 with a 1.72 ERA in six starts with the Stars to
earn his third big league stint in three seasons. Spencer struggled
last year while up with the Padres, going 0-7 with a 9.16 ERA in
two trips to the big leagues.
</P>
<P>
   Kolb is making his first trip to the majors. The 26-year-old
right-hander was 0-1 with a 3.14 ERA and eight saves in 14 games
out of the bullpen with Las Vegas. Whiteside was 1-2 with a 3.21
ERA in 11 relief appearances. He has pitched in the big leagues
every year since 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Lopez went 0-1 with a 10.24 ERA in three starts. After limiting
Atlanta to one run on four hits in seven innings of his major
league debut on April 29, he failed to make it through two innings
in either of last two starts. Palacios was 0-1 with a 6.74 ERA in
seven games out of the bullpen.
</P>
</TEXT>
