<HEADLINE> Clinton Declares Disaster Areas  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JEFFERSON CITY, Mo. (AP) -- President Clinton declared two
eastern Missouri counties federal disaster areas Friday, days after
heavy rains caused flash floods.
</P>
<P>
   Residents in Franklin and Jefferson counties are now eligible
for federal grants and low-interest loans to help rebuild their
homes and businesses, said Jerry Nachtigal, spokesman for Gov. Mel
Carnahan.
</P>
<P>
   As much as15 inches of rain fell Saturday night and Sunday
morning, causing severe flash flooding and killing two people who
became trapped in vehicles by floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
   Carnahan said preliminary information showed more than 500 homes
and businesses were damaged or destroyed. While a final total
damage estimate was not yet available, officials have estimated it
at more than $100 million.
</P>
